cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on modeling a two-layer heterogeneous network and optimizing power consumption for device-to-device communication, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses power control schemes for device-to-device communication, which involves information transmission and signal processing, both of which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a power-efficiency optimization problem for device-to-device communication, which can be viewed as a control problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions outage performance of both D2D layer and cellular layer, which can be related to multimedia quality of service. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry approach to model the two-layer heterogeneous network, which can be related to game theory and optimization.
